regarding data alignment while fetching new crypto, 100 crpyto 1m candles. what happens if the last fethed crpyto is more recent than the first fetched crypto? Do we just align to the oldest one? Or do we have some kind of dynamic alignment?
My honest take: for dev research, this is fine. For production-grade research artifacts, I would eventually add an explicit “closed candle cutoff” and maybe a freshness report per symbol.

One caveat: this is a relatively simple vectorized stress test. It has fees, funding bleed, next-bar execution, volatility parity, pessimistic entry returns, and z-score logic. It does not yet model every production execution concern like order book depth, real slippage curves, precision, partial fills, borrow/funding asymmetry per symbol, or exchange outages.

